            "body": "I just tested further and it looks like the name gets overwritten by `vim.api.nvim_buf_set_name` itself?\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nvim.api.nvim_buf_set_name(0, 'distant://hello.txt')\r\n\r\nprint(vim.api.nvim_buf_get_name(0))\r\n-- Prints \"distant://hello.txt\"\r\n\r\nvim.api.nvim_buf_set_name(0, 'distant+1234://hello.txt')\r\n\r\nprint(vim.api.nvim_buf_get_name(0))\r\n-- Prints \"/Users/senkwich/distant+1234://hello.txt\"\r\n-- where \"/Users/senkwich\" is my cwd\r\n```",
